c5CNet/3 Visual Editor control commands:

c7^X   c6Exit        c2Abort, save, edit, line-editor, new, get, put, quote, or help
c7^C   c6Command     c2Allows you to execute a BBS command such as WHO, TIME,
                 c2STATUS, or OLM.
c7^R   c6Region      c2First Mark a spot, then move to another point to Copy or Kill
                 c2text.  Copied or killed text can be re-inserted at any point
                 c2using the Paste option.
c7^P   c6Preview     c2Display your message exactly as others will read it
c7^S   c6Search      c2Search for a string of characters
c7^U   c6Up          c2Move to the top of the screen, then top of text
c7^O   c6Down        c2Move to the bottom of text
c7^A   c6Page Up     c2Move up one page-full of text
c7^Z   c6Page Down   c2Move down one page-full of text
c7^B   c6Begin       c2Move to the beginning of the current line
c7^N   c6End         c2Move to the end of the current line
c7^V   c6Verify      c2Re-print the current screen
c7^K   c6Kill        c2Erase from cursor to end of line
